                "image": "../../images/badges/cu-as-as.png",
                "description": "<div id=\"body_text\"><h2>Astronomer Activity Badge </h2><img src='../../images/badges/cu-as-as.png' alt='Astronomer Activity Badge ' title='Astronomer Activity Badge ' height='150' width='150' align='right' style='margin-left:10px;'><br><p><p style=\"font-weight: bold;\">To gain this badge, Cub Scouts must complete the following:</p><ol><li><p>Make a model or draw a simple diagram of the solar system.</p></li><li><p>Explain the difference between a planet and a star.</p></li><li><p>Identify three constellations.</p></li><li><p>Find out about and present some information on the two of the following: planets, comets, the northern lights, the sun, eclipses, meteorites, black holes, the moon, light years, space exploration or any other space-related subject.</p></li><li><p>Observe the moon, if possible using binoculars or a telescope. Describe some of its features.</p></li><li><p>Know how to locate and identify the pole star. Know how explorers used it to navigate and plot courses.</p></li></ol></p><p>&nbsp;</p> </div>"
