                "description": "<div id=\"body_text\"><h2>Membership Award </h2><img src='../../images/badges/MES.png' alt='Membership Award ' title='Membership Award ' height='150' width='150' align='right' style='margin-left:10px;'><br><p><p style=\"font-weight: bold;\">When a young person joins the Troop, (regardless of whether he or she was a Cub Scout), to gain this Award, they will be required to:</p><ul type=\"disc\"><li> <p>know about the Troop</p></li><li> <p>get to know other members and leaders in the Patrol and Troop</p></li><li> <p>find out about the ceremonies and traditions in the Troop</p></li><li> <p>find out about the activities that the Patrol and Troop does</p></li><li> <p>know and understand the Scout Promise and Law and the rules of the Troop</p></li><li> <p>know and understand the Scout Motto, sign, salute and handshake</p></li><li> <p>show a general knowledge of the history and family of Scouts and Scouting around the world</p></li><li> <p>know what to do at Investiture</p></li> </ul><p>Once a young person has completed these requirements, and when they feel ready to make their Promise, they can be invested.</p><p><h3>Notes</h3><p><p>There is no fixed timescale for this process. You should discuss timing with the young person.</p></p><p>&nbsp;</p> </div>"
